snippet.textDisplay: Licensing ARM designs is a mistake.  Licensing the ARM instruction set means you can build custom ARM clones like Apple did. Apple has a long history with ARM and they are grandfathered in. They have a perpetual license to the ARM instruction set.  Even if Nvidia were to buy ARM and cease to license the designs it won't stop Apple.  Apple Silicon is ARM only in the fact that it can run ARM instructions but it's design is entirely Apple's.
snippet.textOriginal: Licensing ARM designs is a mistake.  Licensing the ARM instruction set means you can build custom ARM clones like Apple did. snippet.textDisplay: My 5900x has had quite a few issues. It had consistent reproducible hard crashes in premiere when AutoOC was on and random WEAH logger errors with power failure that occurs randomly. After looking into it, this is a common issue. The performance is fantastic, but at this rate, Intel could have them beat in professional industries even if their CPUs are slightly less performant. Stability is very important. It's has lost me a bunch of progress. I'm now in the habit of saving after every action.
